net.sf.opensftp
Class SftpUtilFactory

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtilFactory

public class SftpUtilFactory
extends Object

SftpUtilFactory uses the following strategy to dynamically choose an concrete implementation of SftpUtil to instantiate a singleton object for.

  • Uses the concrete implementation specified through the /opensftp-config/sftputil-impl/@type node in the opensftp-config.xml configuration file.
  • Uses the concrete implementation specified through the net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtil system property.
  • Uses the concrete implementation specified through the first and only effective call to setSftpUtilClassName(String).
  • Otherwise, uses the default implementation class SftpUtil.

NOTE: Among the above approaches, each one has a lower priority than the one before it.

getSftpUtilClassName

public static String getSftpUtilClassName()
Returns the name of the chosen concrete implementation of SftpUtil .

This method will set the name of the concrete implementation of SftpUtil to the default one before return, if the name of the SftpUtil implementation class hasn't been effectively set.

Returns:
the name of the actual SftpUtil implementation class

getSftpUtil

public static SftpUtil getSftpUtil()
Returns the singleton instance of the chosen concrete implementation of SftpUtil.

This method will set the SftpUtil implementation class to the default one before creating a Singleton instance if the name of the SftpUtil implementation class hasn't been effectively set.

setSftpUtilClassName

public static void setSftpUtilClassName(String name)
Sets the name of the SftpUtil implementation class with the specified name.

This method can be used to set the name of the SftpUtil implementation class programmatically rather than via configuration file or system property.

A call to this method is effective only when the following conditions are all met.

  • The /opensftp-config/sftputil-impl/@type node in the opensftp-config.xml configuration file was not or not effectively set. It's not a effective set if you specify a class which doesn't exist in the classpath or doesn't implement SftpUtil at all.
  • The net.sf.opensftp.SftpUtil system property was not or not effectively set.
  • No previous call to getSftpUtilClassName().
  • No previous call to getSftpUtil().
  • The class identified by the specified name exists in the classpath and implements SftpUtil.
  • No previous effective call to this method.

Parameters:
name - Name of the SftpUtil implementation class to set
